title: Agrigrain- The Good Name in Grain

tasks.task: Bill Ringland discusses his family-run AgriGrain business operations.
subtasks: Introduce self and company (Bill Ringland describing AgriGrain).
Explain business location and expansion (Narromine and new Canebel site).
Highlight regional soil diversity (different soil types and crop adaptability).
Describe grain export routes (Port Botany and global destinations).
Comment on third harvest season success in Canebel.
Discuss local grower support and community commitment.
Outline historical grain tonnage in the area.
Emphasize freight cost advantage provided by AgriGrain.
Explain storage and purchasing options for growers.
Describe facility capacity and expansion plans.
